@qinzhaokun Looks fine to me. A couple of minor comments/suggestions
AUTHORS.md - The License header is not in the .md comment format. Other .md files look fine.
.git\* - It should be okay to add the git files to ignore. I believe the RAT default ignore git specific files, if not the it can be explicitly added to exclude list.

@yonzhang  thanks Edward.. yes you are correct..  

"one alert definition should possibly have multiple notification types associated " ,  I missed it :( ..

I'll remove tag and add it into notificationDef  { List of Notifications } .. Another advantage is we can avoid new API :) ..

